# ── SMTP ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# OPTION A — Gmail (recommended, most reliable)
# -----------------------------------------------
# 1. Go to: https://myaccount.google.com/security
# 2. Enable "2-Step Verification" if not already on
# 3. Then go to: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
# 4. Choose "Mail" → "Windows Computer" → click Generate
# 5. Copy the 16-character password (spaces are fine, they are stripped)
# 6. Paste it below:
#
#   SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
#   SMTP_PORT=587
#   SMTP_USER=yourname@gmail.com
#   SMTP_PASS=xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx
#
# OPTION B — Outlook / Office 365 personal (outlook.com, hotmail.com)
# -----------------------------------------------
# 1. Go to: https://account.microsoft.com/security
# 2. Click "Advanced security options"
# 3. Scroll to "App passwords" → Create a new app password
# 4. Paste it below:
#
#   SMTP_HOST=smtp.office365.com
#   SMTP_PORT=587
#   SMTP_USER=yourname@outlook.com
#   SMTP_PASS=your-app-password
#
# NOTE: UBT institutional emails (@ubt-uni.net) usually have SMTP AUTH disabled
# by IT. Use a personal Gmail or Outlook account as the SENDER instead.
# Emails will still be DELIVERED to @ubt-uni.net inboxes.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Fill in your real credentials below, then restart the backend.
# Leave as-is to use DEV MODE (URLs printed to the terminal instead).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your-app-password
